OL,3,GStrathclyde
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FIt will be cloudy as rain
OL,6,Fspreads east through the day, becoming
OL,7,Fheavy at times. It will become drier
OL,8,Fand brighter across Argyll in the
OL,9,Fafternoon.
OL,10,
OL,11,CTonight:FCloudy with rain in the east
OL,12,Fthrough the evening, clearing east
OL,13,Fovernight. Otherwise dry with
OL,14,Fincreasing clear spells from the west,
OL,15,Fallowing a frost to develop.
OL,16,
OL,17,CFriday:FA cold start with some frost,
OL,18,Fand variable cloud in the east.
OL,19,FOtherwise a dry day with increasingly
OL,20,Fsunny spells, but feeling a bit cooler
OL,21,Fthan recent days.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
